verses.text_plain: Wisdom hath builded her house, she hath hewn out her seven pillars:
verses.verse_html: 1Wisdom hath builded her house, she hath hewn out her seven pillars:

verses.text_plain: She hath killed her beasts; she hath mingled her wine; she hath also furnished her table.
verses.verse_html:
2She hath killed her beasts; she hath mingled her wine; she hath also furnished her table. ▼
▼ her beasts: Heb. her killing

footnotes.body_html: ▼ her beasts: Heb. her killing

verses.text_plain: She hath sent forth her maidens: she crieth upon the highest places of the city,
verses.verse_html: 3She hath sent forth her maidens: she crieth upon the highest places of the city,

verses.text_plain: Whoso is simple, let him turn in hither: as for him that wanteth understanding, she saith to him,
verses.verse_html: 4Whoso is simple, let him turn in hither: as for him that wanteth understanding, she saith to him,

verses.text_plain: Come, eat of my bread, and drink of the wine which I have mingled.
verses.verse_html: 5Come, eat of my bread, and drink of the wine which I have mingled.

verses.text_plain: Forsake the foolish, and live; and go in the way of understanding.
verses.verse_html: 6Forsake the foolish, and live; and go in the way of understanding.

verses.text_plain: He that reproveth a scorner getteth to himself shame: and he that rebuketh a wicked man getteth himself a blot.
verses.verse_html: 7He that reproveth a scorner getteth to himself shame: and he that rebuketh a wicked man getteth himself a blot.

verses.text_plain: Reprove not a scorner, lest he hate thee: rebuke a wise man, and he will love thee.
verses.verse_html: 8Reprove not a scorner, lest he hate thee: rebuke a wise man, and he will love thee.

verses.text_plain: Give instruction to a wise man, and he will be yet wiser: teach a just man, and he will increase in learning.
verses.verse_html: 9Give instruction to a wise man, and he will be yet wiser: teach a just man, and he will increase in learning.

tokens.text: and he will be yet wiser

verses.text_plain: The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom: and the knowledge of the holy is understanding.
verses.verse_html: 10The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom: and the knowledge of the holy is understanding.

verses.text_plain: For by me thy days shall be multiplied, and the years of thy life shall be increased.
verses.verse_html: 11For by me thy days shall be multiplied, and the years of thy life shall be increased.

verses.text_plain: If thou be wise, thou shalt be wise for thyself: but if thou scornest, thou alone shalt bear it.
verses.verse_html: 12If thou be wise, thou shalt be wise for thyself: but if thou scornest, thou alone shalt bear it.

verses.text_plain: A foolish woman is clamorous: she is simple, and knoweth nothing.
verses.verse_html: 13A foolish woman is clamorous: she is simple, and knoweth nothing.

verses.text_plain: For she sitteth at the door of her house, on a seat in the high places of the city,
verses.verse_html: 14For she sitteth at the door of her house, on a seat in the high places of the city,

verses.text_plain: To call passengers who go right on their ways:
verses.verse_html: 15To call passengers who go right on their ways:

verses.text_plain: Whoso is simple, let him turn in hither: and as for him that wanteth understanding, she saith to him,
verses.verse_html: 16Whoso is simple, let him turn in hither: and as for him that wanteth understanding, she saith to him,

verses.text_plain: Stolen waters are sweet, and bread eaten in secret is pleasant.
verses.verse_html:
17Stolen waters are sweet, and bread eaten in secret is pleasant. ▼
▼ eaten…: Heb. of secrecies

footnotes.body_html: ▼ eaten…: Heb. of secrecies

verses.text_plain: But he knoweth not that the dead are there; and that her guests are in the depths of hell.
verses.verse_html: 18But he knoweth not that the dead are there; and that her guests are in the depths of hell.
